last_episode_to_air.name: Flatch: Churn Here
last_episode_to_air.overview: It is time for Kelly and Barb to prove why Flatch should be the permanent home of the Butter Bust Museum and she is willing to do whatever it takes! Meanwhile, Shrub has big news to deliver to Lloyd and Mandy is in charge of blessing the town's animals.

name: Welcome to Flatch
overview: When a documentary crew sets out to explore the lives of residents in a small American town – their dreams, their concerns – they stumble upon the midwestern town of Flatch, which is made up of many eccentric personalities. It’s a place you want to visit and maybe even stay. If there was a decent motel. Which there is not.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: The whole town attends the annual Scarecrow Festival, where cousins Kelly and Shrub compete.

episodes.name: Jesus Take the Wheel
episodes.overview: Kelly starts a ride-sharing business called "Kuber," and enlists Shrub as her business partner.

episodes.name: Dance It Out
episodes.overview: When a coveted pair of sneakers lands in a Flatch shoe store, Kelly and Shrub scramble to buy them.

episodes.name: Naked Lady Day
episodes.overview: Father Joe redirects Shrub's graffiti to an art class; Kelly gets some quality time with her father.

episodes.name: That Old Flatch Magic
episodes.overview: Kelly inspires Dylan to return to his passion of magic with a visit to Flatch's new magic shop.

episodes.name: RIP Cynthia
episodes.overview: Kelly and Shrub volunteer at a senior computer class and the town gets a lesson on catfishing.

episodes.name: Sweet Spot
episodes.overview: Kelly and Shrub attempt to do good deeds in town, hoping to get a reward.

episodes.name: Dinners, Dresses, and Dumps
episodes.overview: Kelly plans a special dinner when her dad comes home. Meanwhile, Shrub and Beth start spending a lot of time together and Cheryl breaks out her lucky dress for a date with Jimmy.

episodes.name: The Devil’s Backbone
episodes.overview: To increase their social media following, Kelly and Shrub plan to record a surprise reunion with Father Joe and another former member of his religious boy band, A-men.

episodes.name: On the Hooky
episodes.overview: Shrub gets a new job detailing cars, and Cheryl and Mandy bond over a day of playing hooky.

episodes.name: No Credit/Bad Credit
episodes.overview: As Shrub thrives at his new job and Kelly gets a starring role in the car lot’s commercial, Father Joe begins to miss having them around.

episodes.name: Ghosted
episodes.overview: Kelly and Shrub get lost in the woods on her birthday while Cheryl, Mandy, Nadine and Father Joe decide to host a séance.

episodes.name: Pyramid Scheme
episodes.overview: Kelly's Aunt Lola comes to visit, and Kelly accidentally gets involved in a green juice pyramid scheme. Meanwhile, Father Joe helps Shrub get into college.

episodes.name: Merry Flatchmas
episodes.overview: Kelly's father puts her in charge of the Flatch Christmas celebration, and disaster ensues involving a holiday gift exchange, a fire and Shrub breaking some news to Kelly.

episodes.name: Welcome to (Barb) Flatch
episodes.overview: Barb Flatch makes a triumphant return to her hometown to shake things up. Kelley is changing diapers. Cheryl and Joe are raising baby chickens. Shrub is courting Beth.

episodes.name: Blackout
episodes.overview: A major heatwave leads to a blackout and everyone must band together to stay cool.

episodes.name: Maniflatch Destiny
episodes.overview: Cheryl’s chickens are making enough eggs to go around. Father Joe attempts to teach Shrub to drive. Kelly’s career is taking off as Barb’s brand-new intern.

episodes.name: Open House
episodes.overview: Barb’s first open house in Flatch draws all kinds of attention. Mandy displaces Father Joe as the Flatch advice giver. Kelley rises to the occasion as an up-and-coming real estate agent.

episodes.name: The Headless Horseman
episodes.overview: When a psychic at Barb's spooky ladies' night influences some big changes and sparks some romance, dynamics are forever changed.

episodes.name: Glowing Up is Hard to Do
episodes.overview: Shrub has broken "The Cuz Code" with Kelly by dating her boss; Beth feels jealous, so Kelly steps in to help her win Shrub back.

episodes.name: The Tri-State Real Estate Conference
episodes.overview: Kelly, Barb, and Barb’s new boyfriend, Shrub, all attend a real estate conference together but Barb's ex complicates things; Cheryl decides to focus on her own eggs, enlisting Joe’s help in freezing them

episodes.name: Flatchural Disaster
episodes.overview: Mandy, Barb and Dylan are throwing their hats in the ring for the town 'selectperson,' and everyone is taking sides for their heated town debate. Kelly and Nadine may finally have to bury the hatchet when they need each other most. When a tornado makes its way through the town, Flatch spins out of control.

episodes.name: O Come, All Ye Flatchful
episodes.overview: The Holiday Season has arrived in Flatch and Barb is getting into the Christmas spirit by holding auditions for her very own 'Barbieshop' quartet! Joe is thrilled to show of his musical skills from his former boyband days. When Kelly and Shrub host a toy drive they have their very own Christmas miracle when their hero, Columbus Crew soccer star, Derrick Etienne, makes a special guest appearance.

episodes.name: Flatch or (Butter) Bust
episodes.overview: It's Barb's birthday, but she is not in the mood to celebrate her milestone; Barb is not alone in her blues as Joe is also down in the dumps over his recent breakup with Cheryl; Nadine and Kelly set out to cheer up Barb.

episodes.name: Flatch-elor Party
episodes.overview: t's time for a Flatch-elor Party! Kelly and Shrub are scouting out the perfect location for Kelly's dad's bachelor party. They land on the laser tag park and shots are fired! Meanwhile, Barb calls a townhall meeting about an alleged porch pirate on the loose in Flatch. Barb, Mandy, Cheryl, and Nadine will stop at nothing to uncover this mystery.

episodes.name: What Are You, Chicken?
episodes.overview: The saga of the Flatch porch pirate continues! When Kelly and Shrub realize who the culprit is, they must figure out how to do right by Flatch. Meanwhile, Joe is still missing Cheryl so Barb decides it's time for a makeover fit for a former boy band star before the agricultural fair.

episodes.name: Flatch: Churn Here
episodes.overview: It is time for Kelly and Barb to prove why Flatch should be the permanent home of the Butter Bust Museum and she is willing to do whatever it takes! Meanwhile, Shrub has big news to deliver to Lloyd and Mandy is in charge of blessing the town's animals.
